en.Name: M1911A1 Centennial Edition .45 ACP pistol
en.Description: Commonly known simply as "Colt", the M1911 is one of the most famous handguns on the planet. It went through both World War's as a standard-issue US Army pistol, and despite that it was replaced in 1986, its furher variations are still a sidearm of choice in different US Special Forces. M1911A1 is the further generation of a M1911 pistol, after World War I, the military's Model 1911 went through various changes including shorter trigger with frame cuts, improved sights, an arched mainspring housing and a redesigned grip safety. This gun is the Centennial Edition.

en.Name: TDI KRISS Vector Gen.2 7.62x51 assault rifle
en.Description: A mysterious assault rifle that looks like an enlarged version of the KRISS Vector submachine gun and chambers in .308 Win (7.62x51mm) cartridge. Although it bears the trademark of KRISS, it is not a product of the company, and its designer and manufacturer are unknown. It has an enlarged and heavier bolt to accommodate the high chamber pressure of the .308 rifle bullet.
